#. Tag: title
#: using-kturtle.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using &kturtle;"
msgstr "Utilización de &kturtle;"

#. Tag: screeninfo
#: using-kturtle.docbook:5
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is a screenshot of &kturtle; in action"
msgstr "Esta é unha ilustración de &kturtle; en acción"

#. Tag: phrase
#: using-kturtle.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kturtle; Main Window"
msgstr "A xanela principal de &kturtle;"

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:16
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "The main window of &kturtle; has three main parts: <link linkend=\"the-"
#| "editor\">the editor</link> (1) on the left where you type the "
#| "&turtlescript; commands, the <link linkend=\"the-canvas\">the canvas</"
#| "link> (2) on the right where the turtle make your drawing, and the <link "
#| "linkend=\"the-inspector\">inspector</link> (3) which gives you "
#| "information when your program executes. Besides these you find <link "
#| "linkend=\"the-menubar\">the menu bar</link> (5) from where all the "
#| "actions can be reached, <link linkend=\"the-toolbar\">the toolbar</link> "
#| "(4) that allows you to quickly select the most used actions, the "
#| "<guilabel>Console</guilabel>, that you can use to enter a one line "
#| "command to test it, and <link linkend=\"the-statusbar\">the statusbar</"
#| "link> (along the bottom of the window) where you will find feedback on "
#| "the state of &kturtle;."
msgid ""
"The main window of &kturtle; has three main parts: <link linkend=\"the-editor"
"\">the editor</link> (1) on the left where you type the &turtlescript; "
"commands, the <link linkend=\"the-canvas\">the canvas</link> (2) on the "
"right where the turtle make your drawing, and the <link linkend=\"the-"
"inspector\">inspector</link> (3) which gives you information when your "
"program executes. Besides these you find <link linkend=\"the-menubar\">the "
"menu bar</link> (5) from where all the actions can be reached, <link linkend="
"\"the-toolbar\">the toolbar</link> (4) that allows you to quickly select the "
"most used actions, the <guilabel>Console:</guilabel> input box, that you can "
"use to enter a one line command to test it, and <link linkend=\"the-statusbar"
"\">the statusbar</link> (along the bottom of the window) where you will find "
"feedback on the state of &kturtle;."
msgstr ""
"A xanela principal de &kturtle; ten tres partes principais: <link linkend="
"\"the-editor\">o editor de código</link> (1) á esquerda onde pode escribir "
"as ordes de &turtlescript;, o <link linkend=\"the-canvas\">lenzo</link> (2), "
"á dereita, onde a tartaruga fai o deseño e o <link linkend=\"the-inspector"
"\">inspector</link> (3) que dá información cando se executa o programa. Alén "
"destes, atópanse a <link linkend=\"the-menubar\">barra de menú</link> (5), "
"desde a que se pode acceder a todas as accións, a <link linkend=\"the-toolbar"
"\">barra de ferramentas</link> (4) que permite acceder rapidamente ás "
"accións máis empregadas, a <guilabel>Consola</guilabel>, que permite "
"escribir unha liña de ordes para probala, e <link linkend=\"the-statusbar"
"\">a barra de estado</link> (na parte inferior da pantalla), na que se atopa "
"información referente ao estado de &kturtle;."

#. Tag: title
#: using-kturtle.docbook:19
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Editor"
msgstr "O editor"

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the editor you type the &turtlescript; commands. Most of functions of the "
"editor can be found in the <link linkend=\"the-file-menu\">File</link> and "
"<link linkend=\"the-edit-menu\">Edit</link> menus. The editor can be docked "
"on each border of the main window or it can be detached and placed anywhere "
"on your desktop."
msgstr ""
"No editor é onde se escriben as ordes de &turtlescript;. A maioría das súas "
"funcións atópanse nos menús <link linkend=\"the-file-menu\">Ficheiro</link> "
"e <link linkend=\"the-edit-menu\">Editar</link>. O editor pode acoplarse en "
"calquera bordo da xanela principal ou pode desprenderse e porse en calquera "
"parte do escritorio."

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:21
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You have several ways to get some code in the editor. The easiest way is "
#| "to use an example: choose <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
#| "guimenu><guisubmenu>Examples</guisubmenu></menuchoice> in the <link "
#| "linkend=\"the-file-menu\">File menu</link> and select an example. The "
#| "file example you choose will be opened in the <link linkend=\"the-editor"
#| "\">the editor</link>, you can then use <menuchoice><guimenu>Run</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Run</guimenuitem></menuchoice> from the menubar or "
#| "the <guibutton>Run</guibutton> from the toolbar to run the code if you "
#| "like."
msgid ""
"You have several ways to get some code in the editor. The easiest way is to "
"use an example: choose the <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Examples</guisubmenu></menuchoice> submenu and select an "
"example. The file example you choose will be opened in the <link linkend="
"\"the-editor\">the editor</link>, you can then use the "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Run</guimenu><guimenuitem>Run</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice> menu item (shortcut: <keycombo action=\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</"
"keycap></keycombo>) or the <inlinemediaobject> <imageobject> <imagedata "
"fileref=\"media-playback-pause.png\" format=\"PNG\"/> </imageobject> </"
"inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>Run</guibutton> button from the toolbar to run "
"the code if you like."
msgstr ""
"Hai varias maneiras de ter código no editor. A máis fácil é empregar un "
"exemplo xa feito: escolla <menuchoice><guimenu>Ficheiro</"
"guimenu><guisubmenu>Exemplos</guisubmenu></menuchoice> no <link linkend="
"\"the-file-menu\">menú Ficheiro</link> e escolla un exemplo. O que escolla "
"será aberto no <link linkend=\"the-editor\">editor</link>, e entón poderá "
"empregar <menuchoice><guimenu>Executar</guimenu><guimenuitem>Executar</"
"guimenuitem></menuchoice> na barra de menú ou o botón <guibutton>Executar</"
"guibutton> da barra de menú para executar o código se o desexa."

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:22
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "You can open &turtlescript; files by choosing <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Open...</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgid ""
"You can open &turtlescript; files by choosing the <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Open...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> menu item."
msgstr ""
"Pode abrir ficheiros escritos en &turtlescript; mediante "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Ficheiro</guimenu><guimenuitem>Abrir…</guimenuitem></"
"menuchoice>."

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:23
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The third way is to directly type your own code in the editor or to copy/"
"paste some code."
msgstr ""
"A terceira maneira é escribir directamente o código no editor ou copiar e "
"pegar código desta guía do usuario."

#. Tag: title
#: using-kturtle.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Canvas"
msgstr "O lenzo"

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The canvas is the domain of the turtle, here the turtle draws according to "
"the commands it gets. After getting some code in the <link linkend=\"the-"
"editor\">Editor</link> and executing it, two things can happen: either the "
"code executes fine, and will you most likely see something change on the "
"canvas; or you have made an error in your code in that case the error tab "
"will appear explaining you what mistake you made."
msgstr ""
"O lenzo é a área na que se visualiza o efecto das ordes, na que a tartaruga "
"debuxa segundo a orde que reciba. Tras escribir algún código no <link "
"linkend=\"the-editor\">editor</link>, e executalo poden ocorrer dúas cousas: "
"ou que se execute correctamente o código, e o máis probábel é que vexa algún "
"cambio no lenzo; ou que cometese algún erro no código e aparecerá a lapela "
"de erros cunha mensaxe que explica o erro que cometeu."

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:30
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can zoom in and out the canvas with your mouse wheel."
msgstr "Pode achegar e afastar o lenzo mediante a roda do rato."

#. Tag: title
#: using-kturtle.docbook:35
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Inspector"
msgstr "O inspector"

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The inspector informs you about the variables, the learned functions and "
"show the code tree while the program is running."
msgstr ""
"O inspector informa acercas das variábeis, as funcións definidas e mostra a "
"árbore de código durante a execución do programa."

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The inspector can be docked on each border of the main window or it can be "
"detached and placed anywhere on your desktop."
msgstr ""
"Pode acoplar o inspector a calquera bordo da xanela principal ou pode mesmo "
"desprendelo e poñelo en calquera parte do escritorio."

#. Tag: title
#: using-kturtle.docbook:42
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Toolbar"
msgstr "A barra de ferramentas"

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:43
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Here you can quickly reach the most used actions. The Toolbar also "
#| "contains the <guilabel>Console</guilabel> where you can quickly invoke "
#| "commands, this might be useful in case you want to test a command without "
#| "modifying the content of the <link linkend=\"the-editor\">Editor</link>."
msgid ""
"Here you can quickly reach the most used actions. The Toolbar also contains "
"the <guilabel>Console:</guilabel> input box, where you can quickly invoke "
"commands, this might be useful in case you want to test a command without "
"modifying the content of the <link linkend=\"the-editor\">Editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"Aquí se poden buscar rapidamente as accións máis utilizadas. A barra de "
"ferramentas contén tamén a <guilabel>Consola</guilabel>, desde a que se "
"poden invocar ordes rapidamente; isto pode ser útil se se quere probar unha "
"orde sen modificar o contido do <link linkend=\"the-editor\">Editor</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can configure the toolbar using <menuchoice><guimenu>Settings</"
"guimenu><guimenuitem>Configure Toolbars...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> to "
"better fit your preferences."
msgstr ""
"Pode configurar a barra de ferramentas mediante "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Configuración</guimenu><guimenuitem>Configurar as "
"barras de ferramentas…</guimenuitem></menuchoice> para que se axuste mellor "
"ás súas preferencias."

#. Tag: title
#: using-kturtle.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Menubar"
msgstr "A barra de menú"

#. Tag: para
#: using-kturtle.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the menubar you find all the actions of &kturtle;. They are in the "
"following groups: <guimenu>File</guimenu>, <guimenu>Edit</guimenu>, "
"<guimenu>Canvas</guimenu>, <guimenu>Run</guimenu>, <guimenu>Tools</guimenu>, "
"<guimenu>Settings</guimenu>, and <guimenu>Help</guimenu>. This section "
"describes them all."
msgstr ""
"Na barra de menú atópanse todas as accións de &kturtle;. Agrúpanse nos "
"grupos seguintes: <guimenu>Ficheiro</guimenu>, <guimenu>Editar</guimenu>, "
"<guimenu>Lenzo</guimenu>, <guimenu>Executar</guimenu>, <guimenu>Ferramentas</"
"guimenu>, <guimenu>Configuración</guimenu>e <guimenu>Axuda</guimenu>. Esta "
"sección descríbeos todos."

